main event: Two round, white objects, the size of baseballs, one on top of the other, were observed moving together some distance apart.
interesting points: The objects were observed by someone who happened to be looking south of the horizon while working at a drive-in.
The objects were observed for about 5 minutes.
The observation occurred under cloudy, rainy conditions with a light breeze and poor visibility.
The observer concluded that the objects were likely a reflection of lights, most likely from an automobile.
The report includes detailed weather conditions and wind data at various altitudes.
result: likely explained as a reflection of lights
sighted object: two round, white objects the size of baseballs
